The commercialisation of research out of universities and into burgeoning start-ups is supported by the government via Innovate UK. Over the last 10 years, Innovate UK has distributed E214 million of grants directly to SMEs in the semiconductor space alone.

Direct and indirect support for the semiconductor sector has been provided through Industrial Strategy Challenge Fund challenges, such as: the Driving the Electric Revolution Challenge, investing EUR0 million in electrification technologies including power electronics, electric machines and drives (PEMD); the Digital Security by Design Challenge and; the EUR153 million Commercialising Quantum Technologies Challenge which is driving innovation across a range of sectors including automotive, healthcare, infrastructure, telecommunications, cyber security and defence. All these activities have leveraged further industrial investment in excess of the original grant values.

