_National Security and Investment Act 2021_

The National Security and Investment Act came into force in January 2022 and grants the government greater powers to intervene in acquisitions and investments into entities and assets where those transactions may pose a national security risk. The Act is actor agnostic and interventions are made on a case-by-case basis. There are 17 sensitive areas of the economy53, which are considered more likely to give rise to national security risks. Subject to certain criteria, acquisitions in these areas must be notified to the government.

